\layout Subsection

Continuum Source
\layout Standard


\begin_inset LatexCommand \label{sub:Continuum-Source}

\end_inset 


\layout Standard

Unless specified otherwise, we adopt stellar parameters of a typical classical
 T\SpecialChar ~
Tauri star for the central continuum source, i.e.
 radius (
\begin_inset Formula $R_{*}$
\end_inset 

), mass (
\begin_inset Formula $M_{*}$
\end_inset 

), and effective temperature the photosphere (
\begin_inset Formula $T_{\mathrm{ph}}$
\end_inset 

) are 
\begin_inset Formula $2\, R_{\sun}$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $0.5\, M_{\sun}$
\end_inset 

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $4000\,\mathrm{K}$
\end_inset 

 respectively.
 The model atmosphere of 
\begin_inset ERT
status Collapsed

\layout Standard

\backslash 
citet{kurucz:1979}
\end_inset 

 equivalently 
\begin_inset ERT
status Collapsed

\layout Standard

\backslash 
citet{kurucz:1993} 
\end_inset 

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{\mathrm{ph}}=4000\,\mathrm{K}$
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\log g_{*}=3.5$
\end_inset 

 (cgs) is used to find the photospheric continuum at H
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset 

 wavelength.
 The parameters are summarised in Table\SpecialChar ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{tab:std_parameters}

\end_inset 

.
\layout Standard

The limb-darkening law used for the continuum source is 
\begin_inset Formula $I\left(\mu\right)=I_{0}\left(1+b\mu\right)$
\end_inset 

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu=\cos\theta$
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset 

 is the polar angle.
 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset 

 is a parameter.
 For no limb-darkening case, 
\begin_inset Formula $b=0$
\end_inset 

, and for the Eddington approximation case 
\begin_inset Formula $b=3/2$
\end_inset 

.
 The former is used in all the calculations presented here.
 (Is this an ok assumption for T Tauri's? You need to check this.)
\layout Standard


\begin_inset ERT
status Open

\layout Standard

\backslash 
begin{table*}
\end_inset 


\layout Standard


\begin_inset ERT
status Collapsed

\layout Standard

\backslash 
begin{center}
\end_inset 


\layout Standard


\begin_inset  Tabular
<lyxtabular version="3" rows="3" columns="12">
<features>
<column alignment="left" valignment="top" width="0">
<column alignment="center" valignment="top" width="0">
<column alignment="center" valignment="top" width="0">
