\backslash 
caption{Sample H$
\backslash 
alpha$ model profiles which charactersize the classfication by 
\backslash 
citet{reipurth:1996}. The combination of magnetospherical accretion flow, the accretion disc, and the colliminated wind model can reasonably reproduce wide ranges of H$
\backslash 
alpha$ profiles seen in observations.  The model parameters and short comments are summarised in Table~
\backslash 
ref{tab:classification}. The horizontal axises are velocities in $
\backslash 
kmps$, and the vertical axises are nomalized fluxes.}
