\begin_inset Formula $T_{\mathrm{wind}}$
\end_inset 

models show not only the blue-shifted absorption features, but also the
 red-shifted absorption feature although the latter nerver seems to go below
 the continuum level.
 The blue-shifted feature is clearly caused by the wind; however, the red-shifte
d abosrption at first seems impossible to be explained by the wind absorption
 since the gas in the ouflowing wind located between the magnetosphere and
 an observer is always moving toward the observer (blue-shifted).
